text:
Saini Sir!! ðŸ™ðŸ™ So, Clubaero it is! The beginning and the end. Jab tak udaane ke kabil rhenge tum sab ko yaad karte rhenge. Thanks for all the contribution. Maze to kafi kiye Techmeets mein, workshops mein, helilabs mein lekin sabse zyada maza bitching mein ata tha. 
What I remember the most, is your sense of humour and apki shayri. Keep spreading joy and laughter in this world. In this chaotic world, nearones like you are a must to survive! There is a certain boldness too in your attitude. Keep it up. We resonated a lot. Will stay in touch and all the best for your career. Baki kafi yaddeyin hai jo milke yaad karte hai.

We met at Robo club and then we stayed in touch forever since then. No words for your contribution. Mech mein bhi kafi chapa hai apne. All the best, stay in touch!

text:

text: Aur bhai gajab! Ye dekho khatam hogye sare assignments, exams, quizes, labs. Humare apne chapu coder. We had a perfect combo of a study group. text: Alan bhai! You were our motivation at Drams. That energy and dialogue delivery was unforgettable. Uske baad bhi kafi kand sune hai apke. Fulltu machate hue at every moment in life. Power to you. All the best.

text:
Ram Ram sir ðŸ™! Once upon a time, there were aero guys. Kahani ki shuruat hoti hai aeroclub ke workshop se. Wahan se leker ke har competition, har bitching, har romantic story with dead end, har assignment, har quiz, har lab,  pura dept sath nikala. Epic to get a brother like you. You completed the best study grp ever. And Club ke bhi har din ke alag kaand hai. Jab jab aerospace ke pas rhunga, tum sab ko yaad karunga. We did some real stuff! Atleast guilt mein to nhi jeeyenge. Baki lots of memories, mumbai sagas, acad ran** rone and chill times. Could not have done it without you. Sari cheeze to ab compile nhi ho payegi ab. But we are always in touch so no worries. Kya ghiste the bhai tum, gajab!
Stay high fly high!

text: Hello Bhai! A sense of surprise when I saw you during orientation. Koi to hai jaan pehcan ka. Met before coming to campus. Tab to alag level hota that apka, super chapu. And fir again crossed on campus. Hope to see you again. Stay in touch!

text: Probably the first star from campus to cast in a web series! All the best for your carrer.

text: So Faizan bhai! Robo club was the beginning I guess. Alag level chapter the aap. text: So, you were the first and last in campus jo mere gaal khichta tha. I ain't that chubby and cute anymore. The first image of yours was quite dangerous. text: Dechi bhai. Aap jaise kuch logo ki wajah se apna chota sa pyara sa Aero dept intact rheta tha and synergy rheti thi. Sabke almost same assignments and similar submissions. text: Bhai aap pehle the jiska dassa dekha tha humne. Apna wing cpi average average tha just because of you alone. Then that Agra trips and tumhare parents ke samne JEE rank awkward situations, and aunty ka dantna, GPLs, Bulla sessions,  and the list goes on and on...Anyways we are always in touch. Starting mein wo startup ke thoughts are still very fresh. Agar kuch bhi karna hai,  just a call awayðŸ˜œ. And yeah seriously, Bangkok trip is on you.

text: Arey Migrain wale patient. Team Aerial Robotics. See where it is today. It's because we four decided that day not to shut it down. text: IIMA bhai alag level chapa. Aero mein kafi kuch seeka though: memories, bitching and mass bunk. All the best for the future. kabhi bhi kuch bhi kaam ho, ping me. Stay grounded as you have been and all the best for the future ahead.

text: Aur Hitesh bhai! Aero club it is. Right from day-1 kafi friendly rhe aap. text: Inshu behen! So, Drams that's where we first met. Small-cute aero family kept us bonded. And then SnT. The techmeet glory was a huge point in my life (not just due to standard reasons but it has something to do with past). And a Big big thanks to you for staying with me during that whole blissful period and keeping everyone motivated. Apke Priyank se liye hue aero notes kaafi kaam aye the. And AUV deserved you. Super impressed with your election move. If you remember, I once said that wanted to have a deep discussion with you on the same, though unfortunately never spared a time for that. Aise hi kafi philosophical discussions hai, that are still in todo. Hope to clear that off! and in a nutshell, you were a real "Changemaker". Stay the same in all spirits and enjoy your life to the fullest. Hope to meet you soon. Meanwhile, stay connected!

text: Jassi Bhai! Kuch sapne adhure rhe gaye. But anyways thanks a lot to at least mobilise them. A real Punjabi spirit. Man with discipline and an ideal Sports gensec. That's what you are for us. All the best.

text: Had a lot of fun with you during Aero classes. Indeed a very cheerful guy. Glad to meet you! Hope to see you soon.

text: Bhai ab kya hi likhu. Hum sab E6-D6 kafi close the waise. That's where we began. I had never anticipated ki tu SnT mein ayega. text: So! E6, lots and lots of fun! Kafi chapu wing thi apni and apka bhi kafi maha yogdan rha hai usme. Just one more thing, stay connected as we were. Will live upon those memories instead of writing about them. See you soon. Wo shadi wala prank acha tha by the way ðŸ˜‚

text: Bhai! Bas wo project wale din yaad ate hai. First and probably Last hai jisme itna fraud machaya tha. Things just didn't fell in place with that. Kafi side priorities aati rhi. text: Hey Naveen! So I had not interacted with you before you become the coordinator. But post that, I respected you a lot. You and Tarish kind of revived and rewoken the Astro club. text: Chale fir kal se Gym ðŸ˜‚ The coolest guy I have met on campus. Wing times were amazing! Missing those whenever I think about them! Lovely time indeed. We will anyways be in touch. text: Arey Sir! so the story goes back to dramatics. Indeed those mehnat wale din were definitely memorable. Kafi feel mein kaam karte the aap sir. And asli maza to galaxy mein aya tha. All those nigh outs, plans, amazing music compilations, ek dusre ke roles katna, chillana, sarcasms, ..................and so on. Post that as an HEC, super supportive. And abhi kuch past mahino se, ek bhi aisa meme-post nhi hai jo apne share kiya ho and maza an aya hoðŸ˜‚. Bhai kasam se, gajab sense of humour hai apka. Stay smiling and make other too! This world needs people like you. Really looking forward to stay in contact. All th best!

text: So, Nitesh Madam! Never interacted with you before became coordinator (as far as I remember). But then, you were the one to keep the balance with that three hyper-active co-corrdis. text: Arey sir! Kitna rote ho aap. Lekin jitna hi zyada rote ho utna hi zyada chapte ho. Quite an irony. Frankly, I don't clearly remember when we first met. May be it was clubs, may be it was during your IGVC, or may be it was during OnC, wait a lot of things. Ultimate chapu banan koi inse sikhe. Gsoc baki tha wo bhi ho gaya. This Last course and you doing Dual under a legendary prof. brought us more closer indeed ðŸ˜…. Hope ki Dassa lag jaye tumhara And thanks for everything. Apologies for the rest. text: Nana! Bhai gajab ho aap. Literally. You were one of my motivations during Drams. Joyful nature, bas raise hi hasate rhiye, duniya ko bahut jarurat hai aap jaise logo ki. Baki was a privilege to meet you and will try to stay in loop further!

text: So Aero it is. Things were quite fun just because of some enthusiastic people like you in dept. Chota sa dept. was just like another set of closely bonded group. I think we are the only dept. to attempt a mass bunk and were more or less successful in it ðŸ˜‚. The labs were quite memorable; the funny stuff we did, the TA one was lit. From keeping the chat group active to writing happy teachers day on board to organizing group photos to maintain discord servers and ccd treats from profs., it counts on you. Thanks for keeping and spreading that energy. And I really felt you someone serious about music when I got to know about your albums and anime stuff. Awaiting to see you at greater heights! The ending could always have been better. So, Hey! let's organize a meet for everyone, at least virtually. Stay connected, might need you to develop some music stuff that was pending ðŸ˜‰. All the best!

text: Okay, how about discussing memories on call whenever you'll be reading this years later. We just have too much to write in a little box. WE ARE ALWAYS IN TOUCH! Just stay grounded, stay happy and I know you'll pave your way to your destinies. Yaar ek trip karni hai but.

text: Hmm. So don't know where to begin with. Chapu tum ho, bakait tum ho, cool tum ho, etc. Ye to generic hai but above all, you were really a jolly, selfmotivated person to be with. Yaar apna pura ka pura dept. hai mast tha. We'll cath it up someday when'll meet. We definitely will. And haan, will try to stay in core ðŸ˜‰. Let's defy gravity and fly high! and meet above the zenith!

And we learn them from you. It was a real privilege knowing you. I hope we continue that further and wish to cross over again someday. Meanwhile, Take care and Best wishes.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Okay so first of all, I think our parents met even before we did. I really feel great and admire about how we didn't overwhelm and overreacted ourselves, being from the same state. In fact, I feel the same for all of us. We just balanced it. Whatever we had in common was just crazy; from missing flights to random dinner scheduling. All the very best for your journey ahead, and will love to stay in touch.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: D6's most humble and friendly guy. That's what we remember you for. It's nice to be around people like you. Keep those qualities and all the best!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: So many things. Kya kya likhe. Thanks for helping us in all the SPO stuff. Thanks for helping in Aero stuff and it was fun to study with you, to connect with you. Definitely, Aero mein sab mas the yaar. It was a beautiful little department just because of people like you. Quite a synergy. Last moment assignments exams ka sath baith ke samajna, all those are a great dose of nostalgia. But I guess we met before that, during Udghosh marketing. I know you since then. And we all have lots of karmas to be balanced for you, so please stay in touch. We are just a text away.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Memories ke liye puri zindagi hai, abhi trip plan karte hai.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Barwal bhai! Tumhare bina Drams adhura hai. Galaxy to dur dur tak kar nhi pate agar tum nhi hote. Alag level humour, alag level sentiment, alag level dedication. Ye sab apse sikha hai. Thanks for all that. All the best. You will defininately achieve whatever you envision. Stay in touch!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Got you quite close be it UDGHOSH, Shooting or Elections. You have that kind of winning personality. Keep it safe and you'll conquer whatever you wish for. Quite a learning from you. Baki stay in touch as always and All the best!

author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: So, one of the person whom I truly admire the most on campus. Yeah, we got close during elections. Since then, we always resonated and understood each other. That's what I felt. In this fake world, where people just make baseless claims, someone "real" like you can be a motivation. You are what an ideal being should be. Sound in skills, humble in nature, no faltu bakwas just real solid results, friendly, ethical, and all this rooted to the ground. One big achievement of being associate head was to meet you closely. It was no less than a privilege. Please stay in touch and nurture/pass on all your good qualities. The world needs people like you!
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text:
Arey Sir! We knew each other casually before campus. But then, you were out of my league, somewhere very high. Thanks for the opportunity that we once again met and worked with real dedication here. Udghosh played a huge role, you see. It gave all the required mental fuel, using which we propelled ourselves in whatever we do today. And that too working with you felt like a real team. I doubt my dedication if you had not been there with me. Cheers to that. Looking forward to stay in loop with you ahead. Bhulna mat! 
PS. Range nhi ban rhi.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Bhai Sunit! You were a motivation. Really. Saw you working at the hall, at fests, on other projects, and finally got a chance to prepare a little with you during placements. The dedication was unmatchable. Keep up the good work and yeah, will love to stay in contact with you. All the Best.
author: Mataria Pence Jagatkumar

text: Arey Sir! That's how we greet whenever we met. I always admired you on how you managed multiple things at the same time and excelled in all. There are few people like you who achieve success but keep themselves grounded. A trait of true Maratha! But seriously Arey Sir kya alag level chapter ho aap. I am glad to get a chance to work with you. Stay humble always. And stay happy. All the very best!

text: Just pick up the damn phone, or else we know the address.

Aero was a great time indeed. Sleepy classes, bitching profs, funny labs, explaining to profs how shitty their grading algo is, and lot other mini fun. Thats it I guess. But I admire you a lot. Hope to stay in contact.
